<h1>Acrobat Reader 2.1 Help</h1>

<hr>

<p>Many files on this web site use the Adobe Acrobat format. This
format preserves the original document layout and insures that
the document you view and print will look exactly like the
document that EPD published.</p>

<p>In order to be able to view and print the Acrobat files, you
must have the free <a
href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/readstep.html">Adobe Acrobat
viewer</a>. A viewer is available for most major operating
systems, and a plug-in is available for the latest version of <a
href="http://www.netscape.com/">Netscape Navigator</a>. </p>

<p>Please print this document before continuing, so you will have
these instructions as you install your acrobat viewer.</p>

<blockquote>
    <p><strong><u>To install and configure an Adobe Acrobat
    viewer:</u></strong></p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
    <li><a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/readstep.html">Click
        here to go to the Adobe Acrobat download site.</a></li>
    <li>Follow the instructions to download and decompress the
        viewer for your operating system.</li>
    <li>Configure your web browser to use Acrobat as an external
        viewer.</li>
</ul>

<p>Here's how you can integrate the Acrobat Reader as an external
viewer or &quot;helper application&quot; for:</p>

<p><a
href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/helpers/netscape-mac.html">Netscape
Navigator for Macintosh</a><br>
<a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/helpers/netscape-win.html">Netscape
Navigator for Windows</a><br>
<a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/helpers/mie-mac.html">Microsoft
Internet Explorer for Macintosh</a><br>
<a href="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/helpers/mie-win.html">Microsoft
Internet Explorer for Windows</a></p>

<p>You can follow similar steps with other Web browser
applications. Note that &quot;application/pdf&quot; is the
official assigned MIME type for PDF documents -the file format
used by Adobe Acrobat software.</p>

<ul>
    <li>Your browser is now set up to view and print Adobe
        Acrobat files! </li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h3><a name="req">Windows® Version System Requirements</a></h3>

<ul>
    <li>386-, 486-based, or Pentium-based personal computer </li>
    <li>Microsoft Windows 3.1, Windows 95, or Windows NT 3.5 or
        greater </li>
    <li>4 MB application RAM </li>
    <li>4 MB hard disk space </li>
    <li>1.44 MB 3.5&quot; floppy disk drive </li>
</ul>

<h3><a name="Windows® Version Installation Instructions">Windows®
Version Installation Instructions</a></h3>

<p>The installation process is controlled by the Acrobat
Installer application. This installation will create a program
group named &quot;Adobe Acrobat&quot; and install the new Acrobat
Reader 2.1 application and support files in the c:\acroread
directory. </p>

<p>The installation process does not install ATM, edit any INI
files on your system, and a does not force a restart of Windows
after completion. </p>

<p>To Install Acrobat(TM) Reader 2.1: </p>

<ol>
    <li>From the Windows Program Manager, choose Run from the
        File menu. </li>
    <li>Type: [drive]:\acroread.exe (include the path where you
        saved the file, if applicable)</li>
    <li>Follow the instructions on your screen. </li>
</ol>

<p>Installation requires approximately 4 MB of free hard disk
space. </p>
