<h3>EPD LAUNCHES WORLD WIDE WEB HOME PAGE</h3>

<p>EPD WILL LAUNCH A HOME PAGE ON AUGUST 15. The Home Page
address will be: www.dnr.state.ga.us/epd<br>
In an effort to improve public access to information and
services, establishing an internet presence was identified as a
priority in the strategic plan for the Department of Natural
Resources. EPD's page is a component of the Department's Home
Page.<br>
EPD's Home Page development emphasized placing practical
information on the site in a user-friendly format. The Home Page
will also provide communication links to other state and federal
agencies and to standards-setting organizations referenced in EPD
Statutes and Rules. The Page will initially contain seven
categories of information which will provide users quick access
to EPD rules, public notices, guidance documents and forms. Other
categories will be added in the near future including: databases,
employment opportunities, and environmental education.<br>
A recent version (2.0 or higher) of Netscape or Microsoft browser
will provide best viewing of EPD's web page. All browsers will
work, including those on commercial service providers, but the
EPD WEB may appear differently using other browsers.<br>
Users are encouraged to visit the web site and provide EPD with
feedback on the usefulness of information provided, and how this
technology can be used to better serve our customers. <br>
</p>
