href="epd016.htm">[About]</a></p>

<h3>HAZARDOUS SUBSTANCE REPORTING FEES CHANGED</h3>

<p>The Hazardous Site Response Act establishes hazardous
substance reporting fees for various Georgia facilities including
those which report under the Superfund Amendments and
Reauthorization Act (SARA) Title III. In the 1996 session, the
General Assembly amended fee requirements to begin with the 1996
calendar year reporting period. The changes are:<br>
n Beginning with the 1996 calendar year reporting period,
facilities reporting solely under Section 312 of SARA Title III
will NOT have to pay the $500 fee.<br>
n Beginning with the 1996 calendar year reporting period, a
graduated fee scale will be implemented for those facilities
reporting under Section 313 of SARA Title III. Those facilities
reporting no release for the preceding calendar year pay no fee;
those reporting a release under 1,000 pounds pay $500, those
reporting a release between 1,000 and 10,000 pounds pay $1,000,
and those reporting a release of 10,000 pounds or more pay
$1,500. These fees will be invoiced in 1997 and due by July 1,
1997.<br>
NOTE: these changes do not affect fees that were due July 1, 1996
based on reports filed for the 1995 calendar year. If a facility
was required to report under Section 312 of SARA Title III for
calendar year 1995, a fee of $500 was due by July 1, 1996. If a
facility was required to report under Section 313 for calendar
year 1995, a fee of $1,000 was due by July 1.<br>
For additional information on current or future fee provisions,
contact the Hazardous Sites Response Program at (404) 657-8600.
For information on SARA Title III reporting requirements, contact
Dr. Bert Langley at (404) 656-6905. </p>
</body>
