href="epd016.htm">[About]</a></p>

<h3>CONTRACTOR SELECTED FOR EMISSIONS TESTING PROGRAM</h3>

<p>EPD launched three initiatives this quarter designed to
improve the quality of the air that residents of the Atlanta
region breathe. On May 1, EPD announced its full support of the
metro-wide Clean Air Campaign. The campaign is a public-private
partnership aimed at raising public awareness of the importance
of changing personal habits to help reduce the area's high levels
of ground-level ozone. The Ozone Advisory Program was also
unveiled, which will inform the public through the media when
health risks are increased because the air quality standards for
ground-level ozone are not being met. <br>
After a competitive bidding process, EPD awarded an eight-year
contract to MCI Telecommunications Corporation to manage the
enhanced emissions testing program. Under this new program, all
cars and light trucks manufactured from 1975 to present will
receive upgraded tests to better detect emissions contributing to
ozone pollution. The new air quality initiative will be
implemented in 13 metro-Atlanta counties: Cobb, DeKalb, Fulton,
Gwinnett, Cherokee, Clayton, Coweta, Douglas, Fayette, Forsyth,
Henry, Paulding and Rockdale. <br>
MCI will develop the program and have it operational by October
1. In addition to managing the inspection program, MCI will
develop computer networks and databases to support the program
and launch a major public awareness campaign. They will maintain
a toll free hotline (1-800-449-AIR1) to respond to questions from
the public.<br>
The Atlanta region has been designated a serious non-attainment
area for ozone; the region has aleady experienced three
ozone-exceedance days this year (May 24, June 6, June 30). The
enhanced emissions testing program is a major component of EPD's
plan for meeting state and Federal standards for ozone. </p>

<h3>CALL GEORGIA'S CLEAN AIR FORCE HOTLINE 1-800-449-AIR1 </h3>

<ul>
    <li>Questions about emissions inspections-who has to have it
        done, when, where </li>
    <li>Information about &quot;early bird&quot; inspection
        incentives </li>
    <li>Information about how to get into the testing business</li>
</ul>
</body>
