<h3>NEW GUIDANCE DOCUMENTS</h3>

<ul>
    <li>Floodplain Management National Flood Insurance Program
        Manual (May, 1996). The manual presents a comprehensive
        discussion of floodplain management, the National Flood
        Insurance Program, flood maps, and flood hazard
        mitigation. It will be used as a training tool in
        assisting professional and civic organizations interested
        in learning more about the do's and don'ts of floodplain
        management in Georgia. The manual is a training and
        resource document for those communities contemplating
        participation in the National Flood Insurance Program.
        Contact the Floodplain Management Unit (404)656-6382. <br>
    </li>
    <li>The final Title V Application and Guidance Package,
        version 1.1 (June, 1996) is available at no charge in
        WordPerfect 6.1 format. It is supplied on 3.5&quot; disk
        and contains the Georgia Air Quality Rules, Synthetic
        Minor, SIP, and Permit by Rule Applications. Contact the
        Air Protection Branch at (404)363-7022 to request a copy.
        The package has been mailed to 1350 industries
        potentially subject to Title V requirements.<br>
    </li>
</ul>
