<h3>RIVER CLEAN UP ORGANIZERS SOUGHT</h3>

<p>During the week of October 12-19, 1996 concerned citizens will
work together to clean up Georgia's rivers during the Fifth
Annual Georgia River Clean up sponsored by the Georgia Department
of Natural Resources. Last year, over 400 volunteers worked
approximately 3300 hours and collected over 600 bags of trash
from dozens of rivers, lakes, and creeks. If you are interested
in becoming a volunteer organizer for your organization or
community, call Gaynell Hill in Water Protection at (404)
651-5480. An organizer packet will be mailed to you which
includes a copy of &quot;Organizing and Conducting a River Clean
Up&quot;, sign up sheets for the event, forms for documenting
results, and flyers to use for local advertising. </p>
</body>
