href="epd016.htm">[About]</a></p>

<h3>HSI RELEASED</h3>

<p>A new edition of the state's Hazardous Site Inventory (HSI)
was published July 1. The HSI is a list of sites in Georgia that
are known or suspected of having a release of a regulated
substance above a reportable quantity and which have yet to
demonstrate compliance with state cleanup standards. The 1996
edition includes 336 sites, 12 of which are in Class I (top
priority). 241 are Class II sites, which will be required to
evaluate their compliance with state cleanup standards on a
schedule established for each site by the Director. </p>

<p>The HSI is published at least once a year. A copy is sent to
the Clerk of the Superior Court of each county who is required to
keep the most current copy with the county's deed records so that
anyone may have ready access to it. <br>
The document consists of an introduction, a list of sites
removed, lists of sites sorted by county, site name, site number,
and class, a summary for each site, and a set of 8 maps. Copies
are available from the Hazardous Site Response Program (404/
657-8600) in three formats: bound book ($10.25), a shrinkwrapped
copy ($8.50), and a diskette which includes the entire text as a
WordPerfect 6.1 file but which does not include any maps ($1.00).
Mailing charges are additional.<br>
</p>
</body>
