<h2 align="center">SMALL BUSINESS ASSISTANCE PROGRAM</h2>

<p><br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<p>In accordance with the 1990 Clean Air Act Amendments, the
Georgia Department of Natural Resources created a Small Business
Assistance Program (SBAP). The goal of the SBAP is to help small
businesses comply with clean air requirements. <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<p>The SBAP provides free technical assistance to small
businesses. A small business is defined as one owned or operated
by a person employing less than 100 employees; does not emit more
than 50 tons per year of any regulated pollutant, and emits less
than 75 tons per year of all regulated pollutants. The services
and resources available to small businesses include: <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<ul>
    <li>&quot;Plain English&quot; explanations of state and/or
        federal air pollution rules affecting small businesses<br
        wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
    <li>Permit Assistance <br wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
    <li>On-site compliance assessment visits. (The visits allow a
        determination of compliance without the threat of
        enforcement.)<br wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
    <li>Complaint resolution of air issues<br wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
    <li>Providing confidential assistance in developing
        compliance strategies<br wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
    <li>Representing small businesses on regulatory review and
        updates<br wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
    <li><a href="pressprt.htm">Workshops</a> and seminars on air
        regulations<br wp="br1">
        <br wp="br2">
        </li>
</ul>

<p>In 1996, the Georgia's Small Business Assistance Program
provided assistance to more than 700 businesses. The program
received requests from commercial printers, drycleaners, wood
furniture manufacturers, lumber yards, autobody shops and others. <br
wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<p>The Georgia's Small Business Assistance Program encourages
small businesses to request assistance by calling our Small
Business Ombudsman at (404) 363-7014 or by contacting the SBAP
coordinator at (404) 362-4842. </p>
</body>
</html>
