<h1 align="center">&quot;Georgia Printers' Partnership: Increasing
Profits and Reducing Waste&quot;</h1>

<h2 align="center">A Workshop for Printers</h2>

<p align="center">For additional information </p>

<p align="center">CONTACT: Anita Dorsey-Word </p>

<p align="center">Small Business Assistance Program </p>

<p align="center">(404) 362-4842 <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<p>Atlanta, Georgia - A workshop will be held January 21, 1997,
at the Printing Industry Association of Georgia headquarters in
Smyrna, Georgia. <strong>A second workshop will be held at the
Georgia Environmental Protection Division Training Center on
January 30, 1997. </strong>This 8-hour workshop will help
commercial printers understand state and federal regulatory
requirements. The program is free and sponsored locally by the
Environmental Protection Division/Small Business Assistance
Program, the Pollution Prevention Assistance Division, Georgia
Institute of Technology, Atlanta Gas Light Company, Printing
Industry Association of Georgia and the City of Atlanta--Neighborhood
Environmental Partnership. <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<p>The speakers will include representatives from industry and
state programs. Agenda topics include hazardous waste and water
issues, permitting issues, state and federal regulatory
requirements, pollution prevention, and energy and cost
reductions. <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>

<p>Commercial printers in all disciplines are encouraged to
attend this informative workshop. </p>

<p>For more information and to register for the workshop contact: </p>

<p>Ricky Whitted at (404) 651-5120 or Anita Dorsey-Word at (404)
362-4842. </p>

