<hr width=61%>
<p><a name="Training Notice"><strong>Training Notice</strong> </a></p>
<p>&quot;Financial Assurance Requirements for Solid Waste Handling and Processing Facilities&quot; </p>
<p>Tuesday, December 17, 1996, 8:30 a.m. until 5:00 p.m., at the Atlanta Tradeport Training Facility, 4244 International 
Parkway, Suite 114, Atlanta, Georgia 30354. </p>
<p>On April 9, 1997, a new federal regulation will become effective that: 1) require local government owners and operators of 
solid waste handling and processing facilities to demonstrate financial assurance for maintenance, closure and post-closure 
care, and corrective action; and 2) introduce new financial mechanisms that private-sector owners and operators may use to 
demonstrate financial assurance. The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency and the Environmental Protection Division are 
offering training on the new financial assurance requirements to owners and operators of solid waste facilities in Georgia. <br wp="br1">
<br wp="br2">
</p>
<p><strong>For additional information, contact Rick Cothran at (404) 362-2591.</strong> </p>
