<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Tritium</TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Jim Hardeman">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="whttxtr1.jpg">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Tritium</H2>

<P>Tritium is a radioactive isotope of hydrogen -- it has one (1)&nbsp;proton
and two (2) neutrons. Tritium has a <A HREF="halflife.html">half-life</A>
of 12.28 years. Tritium decays to stable helium-3 (He-3)&nbsp;by emitting
a very low-energy beta particle.</P>

<P>Although tritium me be found in elemental form as well as most organic
forms, the most prevalent form in the environment is tritiated water --
HTO. In the <A HREF="erl.html">Environmental Radiation Laboratory (ERL)</A>&nbsp;and
aboard the <A HREF="mrl.html">Mobile Radiation Laboratory (MRL)</A>, the
concentration of tritium in tritiated water is determined using a <A HREF="ls.html">liquid
scintillation counter.</A></P>

<H2>
<HR width="100%"></H2>

<CENTER><P>[ <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/index.htm">Home</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/news.htm">What's New</A> | <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/toc.htm">TOC</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/feedback.htm">Feedback</A> | <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/search.htm">Search</A>
]</P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P>
<HR width="100%"></P></CENTER>

</BODY>
</HTML>
