<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Joseph M. Farley Nuclear Plant</TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Jim Hardeman">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="whttxtr1.jpg">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Joseph M.&nbsp;Farley Nuclear Plant</H2>

<P>&nbsp;<IMG SRC="farley.jpg" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=225 WIDTH=300 ALIGN=RIGHT></P>

<P>Southern Nuclear Operating Company (SNC) operates the <A HREF="http://www.southernco.com/www/apc/apc.htm">Alabama
Power Company</A> <A HREF="http://www.nrc.gov/AEOD/pib/reactors/348/348toc.html">Joseph
M.&nbsp;Farley Nuclear Plant</A>, located along the banks of the Chattahoochee
River in Houston County, Alabama, and approximately 18 miles southwest
of the city of Blakely, in Early County,&nbsp;Georgia.</P>

<P>EPD&nbsp;has twenty-six (26) thermoluminescent dosimeters (<A HREF="tld.html">TLDs</A>)&nbsp;deployed
around Plant Farley to monitor ambient gamma radiation levels. EPD also
operates two (2)&nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="airsamp.html">air and rainwater samplers</A>
around Plant Farley. During quarterly monitoring visits, EPD associates
collect <A HREF="soilveg.html">soil, vegetation, groundwater</A> and <A HREF="swat.html">surface
water</A> in Early county. Alabama Power company provides samples of <A HREF="milk.html">milk</A>
collected at local dairies, and EPD associates annually collect samples
of <A HREF="sediment.html">sediment </A>and <A HREF="fish.html">fish</A>
from the Chattahoochee River. All samples are analyzed for the presence
of radioactive materials at the Environmental Radiation Laboratory (ERL),
located on the campus at Georgia Tech. Standard analyses include gross
<A HREF="alpha.html">alpha</A>, gross <A HREF="beta.html">beta</A>, <A HREF="tritium.html">H-3
(tritium)</A>, <A HREF="gamma.html">gamma</A> spectroscopy, <A HREF="strontium.html">strontium</A>-90
(Sr-90) and low-level <A HREF="iodine.html">iodine</A>-131 (I-131).</P>

<P>Click <A HREF="fnp_map.html">here</A> for a map of monitoring locations.</P>

<P>With the exception of trace concentrations of activation products such
as cobalt-58 (Co-58)&nbsp;and Co-60 in river sediment, and occasional above-background
concentrations of tritium (hydrogen-3 or H-3) in river water, environmental
monitoring results show no evidence of releases of radioactive materials
from Plant Farley to the environment.</P>

<P>
<HR width="100%"></P>

<CENTER><P>[ <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/index.htm">Home</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/news.htm">What's New</A> | <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/toc.htm">TOC</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/feedback.htm">Feedback</A> | <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/search.htm">Search</A>
]</P></CENTER>

