<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Water Sampling</TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Jim Hardeman">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="whttxtr1.jpg">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Water Sampling</H2>

<P>The Environmental Radiation Program operates seven (7) continuous ISCO&nbsp;water
samplers on the Savannah River. These samplers have been in service since
March 1995. Prior to that date, Program associates collected grab samples
of <A HREF="swat.html">surface water</A> during quarterly monitoring visits.
</P>

<P>Five (5)&nbsp;of the samplers are located adjacent to the <A HREF="srs.html">Savannah
River Site (SRS)</A> at the mouths of site streams where they join the
Savannah River. Each of these five (5)&nbsp;samplers is located in a protective
housing aboard a 12' boat, and is powered by a marine deep-cycle battery.
Solar panels provide power for anchorage lights, required by U.S. Coast
Guard regulations. The other two fixed samplers are located at the New
Savannah Bluff Lock and Dam in Augusta, and the U.S. Highway 301 bridge
in Screven County. </P>

<P>The samplers are programmed to collect four (4)&nbsp;1-gallon weekly
composites. Environmental Radiation&nbsp;Program associates service the
samplers every four (4)&nbsp;weeks. They collect one (1)&nbsp;liter of
water from each weekly sample, and they also prepare in the field a 1-gallon
&quot;monthly&quot; composite. They deliver the composite sample to the
<A HREF="erl.html">Environmental Radiation Laboratory (ERL)</A> for gross
<A HREF="alpha.html">alpha</A>, gross <A HREF="beta.html">beta</A>, <A HREF="tritium.html">tritium
</A>and <A HREF="gamma.html">gamma</A> spectroscopy analyses. Program associates
store the individual weekly samples until analyses on the composites have
been completed.</P>

<P><A HREF="strontium.html">Strontium</A>-90 (Sr-90) and <A HREF="pu.html">plutonium</A>-239
(Pu-239)&nbsp;analyses are performed on quarterly composites.</P>

<H2>
<HR width="100%"></H2>

<CENTER><P>[ <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/index.htm">Home</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/news.htm">What's New</A> | <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/toc.htm">TOC</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/feedback.htm">Feedback</A> | <A HREF="http://www.dnr.state.ga.us/search.htm">Search</A>
]
<HR width="100%"></P></CENTER>

