<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Sequoyah Nuclear Plant</TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Jim Hardeman">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Sequoyah Nuclear Plant</H2>

<P>&nbsp;<IMG SRC="sequoyah.jpg" HSPACE=5 HEIGHT=225 WIDTH=299 ALIGN=RIGHT></P>

<P>Tennessee Valley Authority (TVA) operates the Sequoyah Nuclear Plant,
located in Hamilton County, Tennessee, approximately 8 miles northeast
of Chattanooga. The Sequoyah Nuclear Plant consists of a two (2)&nbsp;Westinghouse
Pressurized Water Reactors (PWR's). Both units are rated at 1183 megawatts
electric (MWe). Unit 1 began commercial operation in July 1981; Unit 2
in June 1982.</P>

<P>EPD&nbsp;has eleven (11) thermoluminescent dosimeters (<A HREF="tld.html">TLDs</A>)&nbsp;deployed
around Sequoyah to monitor ambient gamma radiation levels. During quarterly
monitoring visits, EPD associates collect <A HREF="soilveg.html">soil,
vegetation</A> and <A HREF="gwat.html">groundwater</A> in Catoosa,&nbsp;Dade,
Walker and Whitfield counties. All samples are analyzed for the presence
of radioactive materials at the Environmental Radiation Laboratory (<A HREF="erl.html">ERL</A>),
located on the campus at Georgia Tech. Standard analyses include gross
<A HREF="alpha.html">alpha</A>, gross <A HREF="beta.html">beta</A>, <A HREF="tritium.html">H-3
(tritium)</A>, and <A HREF="gamma.html">gamma </A>spectroscopy.</P>

<P>Click <A HREF="seq_map.html">here</A> for a map of monitoring locations.</P>

<P>EPD&nbsp;environmental monitoring results show no evidence of the release
of radioactive materials to the environment from the Sequoyah Nuclear Plant.</P>

<P>
<HR width="100%"></P>

