<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>Half-Life</TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Jim Hardeman">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="whttxtr1.jpg">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Half-Life</H2>

<P>Each radioactive material has its own characteristic half-life. Half-life
is defined as the time required for half of the radioactive atoms in a
sample of a radioactive material to decay. Half-lives of radioactive materials
found in nature range from seconds to billions of years. </P>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="halflife.jpg" HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 HEIGHT=273 WIDTH=338 ALIGN=LEFT></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P>To calculate the amount of <A HREF="activity.html">activity</A>
<B><I>A</I></B> remaining at time <B><I>t</I></B> in a sample of a material
with a half-life of <B><I>t<SUB>h</SUB></I></B> with an intial activity
<B><I>A<SUB>0</SUB></I></B>, first calculate the number of half-lives:</P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>n = t / t<SUB>h</SUB></I></B></P></CENTER>

<P>The activity at time <B><I>t</I></B> may then be calculated as:</P>

<CENTER><P><B><I>A = A<SUB>0</SUB> / 2<SUP>n</SUP></I></B></P></CENTER>

<H3><SUP>Examples</SUP></H3>

<P>The half-life of iodine-131 (I-131)&nbsp;is approximately 8 days. Assume
that you have a sample that has an initial activity today of 1 Curie (Ci).
What would be the I-131 activity 16 days from now?</P>

<CENTER><P><B><I>Given: A<SUB>0</SUB> = 1 Ci, t = 16 days, t<SUB>h </SUB>=<SUB>
</SUB>8 days</I></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>n = t / t<SUB>h </SUB>= 16 days / 8 days = 2</I></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>A = A<SUB>0</SUB> / 2<SUP>n </SUP>= 1 Ci / 2<SUP>2</SUP>
= 1 Ci / 4 = 0.25 Ci</I></B></P></CENTER>

<P>Thus, after 2 half-lives, the initial activity is reduced by a factor
of 4. What would the activity of the sample be after 80 days?</P>

<CENTER><P><B><I>Given: A<SUB>0</SUB> = 1 Ci, t = 80 days, t<SUB>h </SUB>=<SUB>
</SUB>8 days</I></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>n = t / t<SUB>h </SUB>= 80 days / 8 days = 10</I></B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>A = A<SUB>0</SUB> / 2<SUP>n </SUP>= 1 Ci / 2<SUP>10 </SUP>=
1 Ci / 1,024 = 0.000977 Ci</I></B></P></CENTER>

<P>After ten (10)&nbsp;half-lives, the <A HREF="activity.html">activity</A>
in the sample has been reduced to less that one one-thousandth (1 / 1,
000 or 0.001) of its initial value.</P>

<P>
<HR width="100%"></P>

