<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE></TITLE>
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Jim Hardeman">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0b5aGold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="whttxtr1.jpg">

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Concentration</H2>

<P>Quantities of radioactive materials present in environmental media are
expressed as concentrations, or <A HREF="activity.html">activity</A> per
unit mass or volume. EPD&nbsp;expresses concentrations of radioactive materials
in solid media (i.e. soil, sediment, vegetation, crops, fish) in <A HREF="activity.html">picoCuries</A>
per kilogram (pCi/kg). EPD expresses concentrations of radioactive materials
in liquid media (i.e. water, rain) in <A HREF="activity.html">picoCuries</A>
per liter (pCi/l). EPD expresses concentrations of radioactive materials
in air in <A HREF="activity.html">femptoCuries</A> per cubic meter (fCi/m^3)
of air. Tritium analyses in all media are currently expressed as <A HREF="activity.html">picoCuries</A>
per liter of free water.</P>

<H2>
